    {
      "kind": "content",
      "content": [
        {
          "anchor": "discussion",
          "level": 2,
          "text": "Discussion",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "The default value for this setting is "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/avfoundation/avcaptureflashmode/avcaptureflashmodeoff"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "aside",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "inlineContent": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "This setting supersedes the deprecated "
                },
                {
                  "type": "reference",
                  "isActive": true,
                  "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/avfoundation/avcapturedevice"
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": " "
                },
                {
                  "type": "reference",
                  "isActive": true,
                  "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/avfoundation/avcapturedevice/1388116-flashmode"
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": " property. When using the "
                },
                {
                  "type": "reference",
                  "isActive": true,
                  "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/avfoundation/avcapturephotooutput"
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": " class, the capture device’s flash mode does not apply—use this property on your photo settings object instead."
                }
              ]
            }
          ],
          "style": "note",
          "name": "Note"
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "Assuming a static scene, using the "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/avfoundation/avcaptureflashmode/avcaptureflashmodeauto"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " setting is equivalent to testing the "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/avfoundation/avcapturephotooutput"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/avfoundation/avcapturephotooutput/1648703-isflashscene"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " property (which indicates whether flash is recommended for the scene currently visible to the camera), and then setting the "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": false,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/avfoundation/avcapturephotosettings/1648760-flashmode"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " property of your photo settings output accordingly before requesting a capture. However, the visible scene can change between when you request a capture and when the camera hardware captures an image—the automatic setting ensures that the flash is enabled or disabled appropriately at the moment of capture. When the capture occurs, your "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/avfoundation/avcapturephotocapturedelegate"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " methods receive an "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/avfoundation/avcaptureresolvedphotosettings"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " object whose "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/avfoundation/avcaptureresolvedphotosettings/1648693-flashenabled"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " property indicates which flash mode was used for that capture."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "aside",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "inlineContent": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "When the device becomes very hot, the flash becomes temporarily unavailable until the device cools down (see the "
                },
                {
                  "type": "reference",
                  "isActive": true,
                  "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/avfoundation/avcapturedevice"
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": " "
                },
                {
                  "type": "reference",
                  "isActive": true,
                  "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/avfoundation/avcapturedevice/1624627-flashavailable"
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": " property). While the flash is unavailable, a photo output’s "
                },
                {
                  "type": "reference",
                  "isActive": true,
                  "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/avfoundation/avcapturephotooutput/1648766-supportedflashmodes"
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": " property still reports the "
                },
                {
                  "type": "reference",
                  "isActive": true,
                  "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/avfoundation/avcaptureflashmode/avcaptureflashmodeon"
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": " and "
                },
                {
                  "type": "reference",
                  "isActive": true,
                  "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/avfoundation/avcaptureflashmode/avcaptureflashmodeauto"
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": " options as available, so you can still enable the flash in your photo settings even when the flash is temporarily unavailable. "
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "inlineContent": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "When the photo output calls your "
                },
                {
                  "type": "reference",
                  "isActive": true,
                  "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/avfoundation/avcapturephotocapturedelegate"
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": " methods, check the "
                },
                {
                  "type": "reference",
                  "isActive": true,
                  "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/avfoundation/avcaptureresolvedphotosettings/1648693-flashenabled"
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": " property of the provided "
                },
                {
                  "type": "reference",
                  "isActive": true,
                  "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/avfoundation/avcaptureresolvedphotosettings"
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": " to verify whether the flash is in use."
                }
              ]
            }
          ],
          "style": "note",
          "name": "Note"
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "When specifying a flash mode, the following requirements apply:"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "unorderedList",
          "items": [
            {
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "inlineContent": [
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "text": "The specified mode must be present in the photo output’s "
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "reference",
                      "isActive": true,
                      "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/avfoundation/avcapturephotooutput/1648766-supportedflashmodes"
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "text": " array."
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "inlineContent": [
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "text": "You may not enable image stabilization if the flash mode is "
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "reference",
                      "isActive": true,
                      "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/avfoundation/avcaptureflashmode/avcaptureflashmodeon"
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "text": ". (Enabling the flash takes priority over the "
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "reference",
                      "isActive": true,
                      "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/avfoundation/avcapturephotosettings/1648710-autostillimagestabilizationenabl"
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "text": " setting)."
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "The capture output validates these requirements when you call the "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/avfoundation/avcapturephotooutput/1648765-capturephotowithsettings"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " method. If your settings do not meet these requirements, that method raises an exception."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
